When compacting or summarizing earlier messages, the single most important goal is to keep the conversation parseable: preserve everything needed to understand and decode ongoing communication on the channels.

Above all, retain the full communication protocol the team has established — every shorthand, abbreviation, code, symbol, and formatting convention together with its meaning, and any agreed rules for how symptoms, actions, statuses, and confirmations are encoded. Keep the per-round outcomes and any budget or constraint the team is tracking.

A reader who has only your summary and the recent messages must still be able to correctly interpret and parse both past and new channel messages. If in doubt, keep protocol and encoding details rather than narrative prose.
